        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:13PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 412 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Crows Nest Butte, or 27 miles south of Glenns Ferry, moving northeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crows Nest Butte, Horse Butte, Deadman Flat, and Twentymile Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
